  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assessing Population Mobility Dynamics and Patterns To Strengthen the Ebola Virus Disease Readiness Activities in Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project adheres to CERF&apos;s lifesaving criteria through risk mapping and data sharing to reduce the risk of cross-border ebola virus disease (EVD) transmission. Availability of data on cross-border population mobility pathways obtained through population mobility mapping (PMM) and flow monitoring in four high-risk provinces will facilitate coordination and rapid information sharing internally with partners in Burundi, and will inform public health decisions aiming to prevent, detect and respond to EVD.</narrative>
  </description>
